This Fock space operator is not yet adapted to its immediate insertion into a 
perturbation calculation.
Remember that a quantum mechanical perturbation calculation requires the
combination of a perturbation term with a projection operator onto the basic 
state space. Therefore, we still have to incorporate a suitable projection 
mechanism onto our two-particle basic.

We will achieve this by collecting only those terms of () that 
contribute if we evaluate this operator for two-particle states with momentum 
 of a given (irreducible) two-particle state space .

